PROGRAM-ID. FILEMERGER.
AUTHOR. SIMON MIKKELSEN.
* Ahoy! This be a program to merge two files into one, ye scallywags.
* It reads from two input files and writes the contents to a single output file.
* Ye best be ready to sail through the seas of code, matey!

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE1 ASSIGN TO 'INPUT1.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE2 ASSIGN TO 'INPUT2.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'OUTPUT.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE1.
01  INPUT-RECORD1 PIC X(100).

FD  INPUT-FILE2.
01  INPUT-RECORD2 PIC X(100).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-EOF1 PIC X VALUE 'N'.
01  WS-EOF2 PIC X VALUE 'N'.
01  WS-TEMP PIC X(100).
01  WS-FRODO PIC X(100).
01  WS-GOLLUM PIC X(100).
01  WS-UNUSED-VAR PIC X(100).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PROCEDURE.
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE1
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE2
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE
    PERFORM UNTIL WS-EOF1 = 'Y' AND WS-EOF2 = 'Y'
     PERFORM READ-FILE1
     PERFORM READ-FILE2
     PERFORM WRITE-OUTPUT
    END-PERFORM
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE1
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE2
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE
    STOP RUN.

READ-FILE1.
    IF WS-EOF1 NOT = 'Y'
     READ INPUT-FILE1 INTO WS-FRODO
     AT END
         MOVE 'Y' TO WS-EOF1
     NOT AT END
         MOVE WS-FRODO TO WS-TEMP
     END-READ
    END-IF.

READ-FILE2.
    IF WS-EOF2 NOT = 'Y'
     READ INPUT-FILE2 INTO WS-GOLLUM
     AT END
         MOVE 'Y' TO WS-EOF2
     NOT AT END
         MOVE WS-GOLLUM TO WS-TEMP
     END-READ
    END-